casebody.data:
Disciplinary Counsel v. Hughes.

[Cite as Disciplinary Counsel v. Hughes, 137 Ohio St.3d 1204, 2013-Ohio-4355.]

(No. 2005-1156 Submitted September 30, 2013 Decided October 2, 2013.)

{¶ 1} This cause came on for further consideration upon the filing of an application for reinstatement by respondent, Jennifer Krieger Hughes, Attorney Registration No. 0063961, last known business address in Miamisburg, Ohio.

{¶ 2} The court, coming now to consider its order of March 22, 2006, wherein the court, pursuant to Gov.Bar R. V(6)(B)(3), suspended respondent for a period of two years, with one year stayed on conditions, finds that respondent has substantially complied with that order and with the provisions of Gov.Bar R. V(10)(A).

{¶ 3} Therefore, it is ordered by this court that respondent is reinstated to the practice of law in the state of Ohio.

{¶ 4} It is further ordered that the clerk of this court issue certified copies of this order as provided for in Gov.Bar R. V(8)(D)(1), that publication be made as provided for in Gov.Bar R. V(8)(D)(2), and that respondent bear the costs of publication.

O’Connor, C.J., and Pfeifer, O’Donnell, Lanzinger, Kennedy, French, and O’Neill, JJ., concur.
